      image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1594736797933-d0501ba2fe65?w=800&q=75&auto=format&fit=crop",
      content: ["<p>Studies show 93% of consumers check Google reviews before buying. Your Google rating isn't just a vanity metric — it's a conversion tool, a trust signal, and an SEO asset. Most businesses treat it as an afterthought. The ones that don't are quietly outcompeting everyone around them.</p>\n<h2>Why Your Google Rating Directly Impacts Revenue</h2>\n<p>A business with 4.8 stars and 200 reviews will get 35–50% more clicks in local search than a 3.9-star competitor — even if the 3.9-star business ranks higher. Conversion rate from profile visit to enquiry is 2–3x higher for businesses with 4.5+ ratings. Google uses review count and rating as local ranking signals.</p>\n<h2>The Review Acquisition System</h2>\n<p>The highest-performing method: WhatsApp-based review requests. After a positive interaction, send a WhatsApp message with the direct Google review link. Conversion rate: 25–40% (vs 2–5% for email). Time the ask: within 24 hours of a positive experience. Never offer incentives — Google prohibits this and it backfires.</p>\n<h2>Responding to Reviews (Both Good and Bad)</h2>\n<p>Respond to every review within 24 hours. Positive reviews: thank them and reinforce one key value your business provided. Negative reviews: acknowledge, apologise (even if not fully at fault), offer to resolve offline. Never argue publicly.</p>\n<h2>Turning Your Rating Into a Sales Asset</h2>\n<p>Add your Google rating to your website homepage, proposal templates, and ad creatives. A 4.8 stars on Google badge increases landing page conversion by 15–25%. Feature your best reviews in WhatsApp follow-ups to warm leads.</p>"],
