      slug: "content-marketing-b2b-lead-generation",
      category: "Content Marketing",
      categoryColor: "bg-pink-100 text-pink-700",
      title: "Content Marketing for B2B: How to Generate Leads with Every Article You Publish",
      excerpt: "B2B content marketing done right converts readers into sales pipeline. Covers topic selection, lead magnets, and distribution strategies for Indian B2B brands.",
      author: "Aetherank Team",
      date: "April 5, 2026",
      readTime: "8 min read",
      image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1552664730-d307ca884978?w=800&q=75&auto=format&fit=crop",
      content: ["<p>B2B content marketing done right converts readers into sales pipeline. The biggest mistake Indian B2B companies make: publishing content that educates without converting. Every article should have a clear path from reader to lead.</p>\n<h2>Topic Selection: Target Buyer Problems, Not Industry News</h2>\n<p>The best B2B content targets specific problems your buyers face. Instead of Digital Marketing Trends 2026, write How to Reduce Cost Per Lead for IT Services Companies. Problem-specific content attracts buyers, not just readers. Use your sales team as your best source of topic ideas.</p>\n<h2>The Content-to-Lead Conversion Framework</h2>\n<p>Every piece of content needs: a primary CTA (book a call, request a demo), a secondary CTA (download a related resource, subscribe), and a content upgrade (a deeper resource exchanged for an email — checklist, template, calculator, benchmark report).</p>\n<h2>Lead Magnets That Actually Convert in Indian B2B</h2>\n<p>ROI calculators to show potential savings. Benchmark reports on how Indian companies in your industry allocate marketing budget. Checklists and audits relevant to your service. Case studies showing how similar companies reduced CAC or increased conversions.</p>\n<h2>Distribution: Most B2B Content Dies in Draft</h2>\n<p>Publish then share on LinkedIn personal and company pages, email to subscriber list, share in relevant WhatsApp groups, repurpose as a LinkedIn carousel. Most B2B content gets 90% of its traffic in the first 48 hours after publication — unless SEO-optimised for long-term organic.</p>"],
