      image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1611162616305-c69b3fa7fbe0?w=800&q=75&auto=format&fit=crop",
      content: ["<p>A platform-by-platform breakdown of Instagram vs LinkedIn for Indian brands — covering audiences, content formats, organic reach, and paid advertising.</p>\n<h2>Instagram: India B2C Powerhouse</h2>\n<p>650 million plus Indian users. Primarily B2C: fashion, beauty, food, lifestyle, fitness, D2C products, local services, restaurants. Best organic reach: Reels (5-8x vs static posts). Best paid: Click-to-WhatsApp campaigns for service businesses, catalogue ads for e-commerce.</p>\n<h2>LinkedIn: India B2B Growth Channel</h2>\n<p>130 million plus Indian users. Primarily B2B: SaaS, professional services, consulting, recruiting, finance, IT services, agencies. Best organic reach: personal profile posts (company pages get 5-10x less reach). Best paid: Lead Gen Forms (collect leads without leaving LinkedIn).</p>\n<h2>When to Use Both</h2>\n<p>B2B companies with a consumer touchpoint benefit from both. Instagram builds brand desirability; LinkedIn drives direct B2B leads.</p>\n<h2>The Decision Framework</h2>\n<p>Are you selling to businesses or consumers? LinkedIn vs Instagram. Is your product visual and lifestyle-oriented? Instagram wins. Is your sales cycle long with high contract values? LinkedIn wins. Do you need scale at low cost? Instagram has 5x more users in India.</p>"],
