      slug: "google-ads-vs-meta-ads-roi-india-2026",
      category: "PPC",
      categoryColor: "bg-purple-100 text-purple-700",
      title: "Google Ads vs Meta Ads in 2026: Which Delivers Better ROI for Indian Businesses?",
      excerpt: "An in-depth comparison of Google Ads and Meta Ads for Indian businesses — covering cost, intent, reach, and when to use each platform for maximum ROI.",
      author: "Aetherank Team",
      date: "April 5, 2026",
      readTime: "7 min read",
      image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1611162617474-5b21e879e113?w=800&q=75&auto=format&fit=crop",
      content: ["<p>An in-depth comparison of Google Ads and Meta Ads for Indian businesses — covering cost, intent, reach, and when to use each platform for maximum ROI.</p>\n<h2>The Core Difference: Intent vs Interruption</h2>\n<p>Google Ads = demand capture. Users are actively searching for your product or service. High intent, ready to buy. Meta Ads = demand generation. You interrupt users browsing their feed. Lower intent, but massive reach. Neither is better — they serve different stages of the customer journey.</p>\n<h2>Cost Comparison (India, 2026)</h2>\n<p>Google Search CPC: Rs 20 to Rs 350 depending on industry. Meta CPM: Rs 40 to Rs 200 for most audiences. Cost per Lead: Google leads are 40-60% more expensive but close 2-3x more often. Meta leads need more nurturing.</p>\n<h2>When Google Wins</h2>\n<p>High-intent categories: legal, financial, healthcare, real estate, home services. When users are actively searching for your exact service. When your landing page converts well and you have clear search volume.</p>\n<h2>When Meta Wins</h2>\n<p>Building brand awareness for new products. Fashion, beauty, lifestyle, D2C categories where discovery drives purchase. When you need scale at lower cost per impression. When retargeting website visitors who did not convert.</p>\n<h2>The Integrated Approach (Best ROI)</h2>\n<p>Most Indian businesses with Rs 1 lakh plus per month budget see best results from: 60% Google Search (capture existing demand) plus 30% Meta (generate new demand and retarget) plus 10% YouTube (awareness).</p>"],
