      slug: "how-to-rank-1-on-google-2026-seo-guide-india",
      category: "SEO",
      categoryColor: "bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700",
      title: "How to Rank #1 on Google in 2026: A Complete SEO Guide for Indian Businesses",
      excerpt: "Learn the exact SEO strategies that drive first-page rankings for Indian businesses in 2026 — from technical audits to link building and GEO optimisation.",
      author: "Aetherank Team",
      date: "April 5, 2026",
      readTime: "8 min read",
      image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1432888498266-38ffec3eaf0a?w=800&q=75&auto=format&fit=crop",
      content: ["<p>Learn the exact SEO strategies that drive first-page rankings for Indian businesses in 2026 — from technical audits to link building and GEO optimisation.</p>\n<h2>Step 1: Technical SEO Foundation</h2>\n<p>Before any content or links: fix your technical base. Run a Screaming Frog crawl — fix all 4xx errors, redirect chains, duplicate content, and missing meta tags. Ensure Core Web Vitals pass (LCP under 2.5s, CLS under 0.1, INP under 200ms). Submit an XML sitemap to Google Search Console. Implement schema markup for your business type.</p>\n<h2>Step 2: Keyword Research for India</h2>\n<p>Target keywords with buying intent, not just traffic. Use Ahrefs or Semrush for keyword research. Prioritise low-competition, high-intent keywords to build early wins. Include regional language keywords — Hindi search volume is massive and largely underserved by competitors.</p>\n<h2>Step 3: On-Page Optimisation</h2>\n<p>Primary keyword in: H1, first 100 words, meta title, URL, at least 2 H2s. LSI keywords throughout. Internal links to 3-5 related pages. External links to 1-2 authoritative sources. Alt text on all images. Aim for comprehensive coverage — if competitors top articles are 1,500 words, write 2,500.</p>\n<h2>Step 4: Link Building</h2>\n<p>Backlinks remain the number one ranking factor. Quality over quantity — 10 links from DA 50+ sites beat 500 links from DA 10 directories. Tactics that work in India: guest posting on YourStory, Inc42, Entrepreneur India; PR mentions in business publications; resource link building.</p>\n<h2>Step 5: Content Velocity and Topical Authority</h2>\n<p>Google rewards websites that comprehensively cover a topic area. Build topic clusters: 1 pillar page (comprehensive 3,000+ word guide) plus 8-12 supporting articles on related sub-topics, all internally linked. This topical authority approach is the most reliable path to consistent page-1 rankings in 2026.</p>"],
